LEXSense.DefinitionShort: = process or action by which living creatures perceive something, primarily --though not necessarily exclusively-- with their eyes, either as a spontaneous incident or as the result of focusing the eyes on something
= process by which humans, deities, or objects become perceptible, primarily --though not necessarily exclusively-- to the eye
= action by which humans look at one another
= causative action by which humans or deities cause humans to perceive something, primarily --though not necessarily exclusively-- with their eyes
literally: to see the light; hence: = state in which humans are alive

Glosses.Gloss: to see the light > to live

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: literally: to see the sub; hence: = state in which humans are alive

Glosses.Gloss: to see the sun > to live

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: literally: to see sleep; hence: = state in which humans are able to sleep

Glosses.Gloss: to see sleep > to find sleep

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: literally: to see death; hence: = process by which humans die
literally: to see the pit; hence: = process by which humans die
literally: to see good; hence: = state in which humans experience well-being
literally: to cause to see good; hence: = causative action by which humans cause humans to experience well-being

Glosses.Gloss: to cause to see good > to make prosper

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: literally: to see life; hence: = state in which humans experience well-being
literally: to see (someone's) face; hence: = state in which humans are in the close presence of someone of a higher social status, such as a ruler, or even God himself

Glosses.Gloss: to see (someone's) face > to be in (someone's) presence

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: literally: to see evil; hence: = state in which humans suffer harm
